<subSubSection pageNumber="328" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="328">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="328">Note:</emphasis>
Underwood clearly designated the cited Sloane plate as the type, pre-dating the choice made by Weatherby (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="328">Contr. Gray Herb.</emphasis>
114: 20. 1936) of 1250.22 (LINN). Unfortunately, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sloane’s">Sloane's</normalizedToken>
plant appears to be identifiable as 
<taxonomicName authority="Sw." authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1829" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1759" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="auritum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="328">A. auritum</emphasis>
Sw.
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="328">A. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
though most authors have adopted 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Weatherby’s">Weatherby's</normalizedToken>
type choice. However, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Underwood’s">Underwood's</normalizedToken>
choice has priority, and it appears that a proposal for the conservation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="328">A. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a conserved type, may be necessary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
